content:
This game is really fun to play and has interesting controls. They are a 
little complex, like it is a bit hard to pull off boosting while 
accelerating (since they are controlled by the same thumb), but otherwise 
very intuitive. The only issues I have are related to sound delays, and 
lagging (I use a Razer phone, and I do see scenarios where the game is 
crispy clear at times, so I wonder if there is a software bug that causes 
both the sound and frame lag issues). The background soundtrack plays 
constantly, and sometimes I hear the random character noises, but I usually 
either not hear a noise that is supposed to prompt (like hitting a 
checkpoint or using the boost), or the noise comes in at least one second 
late. This glitch happens during the adventure menu screen as well. If 
these glitches are fixed, this game will command a lot more of my time than 
it already does.
